[{"id":1377123888,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>A mass M is suspended by a rope from a rigid support at A as shown in figure. Another rope is tied at the end B, and it is pulled horizontally with a force F. If the rope AB makes an angle $\\theta$ with the vertical in equilibrium, then the tension in the string AB is :</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mqlg8jqk/efe26c4f-41e2-4aab-bc9f-302d23f7b169/fcdfd2c0-6c26-11f1-950e-c12a034ebedd/file-6y3zli1mqlg8jql.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mqlg8jqk/efe26c4f-41e2-4aab-bc9f-302d23f7b169/fcdfd2c0-6c26-11f1-950e-c12a034ebedd/file-6y3zli1mqlg8jql.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","question":"<p>A mass M is suspended by a rope from a rigid support at A as shown in figure. Another rope is tied at the end B, and it is pulled horizontally with a force F. If the rope AB makes an angle $\\theta$ with the vertical in equilibrium, then the tension in the string AB is :</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mqlg8jqk/efe26c4f-41e2-4aab-bc9f-302d23f7b169/fcdfd2c0-6c26-11f1-950e-c12a034ebedd/file-6y3zli1mqlg8jql.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mqlg8jqk/efe26c4f-41e2-4aab-bc9f-302d23f7b169/fcdfd2c0-6c26-11f1-950e-c12a034ebedd/file-6y3zli1mqlg8jql.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","options":["<p>$F \\sin \\theta$</p>","<p>$F \\sin \\theta$</p>","<p>$F \\cos \\theta$</p>","<p>$F \\cos \\theta$</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mqlgcjwz","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":1377147713,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>Two persons are holding a light rope tightly at its ends so that it is horizontal. A 15 kg weight is attached to the rope at the midpoint which now no longer remains horizontal. The minimum tension required to completely straighten the rope is :</p>","question":"<p>Two persons are holding a light rope tightly at its ends so that it is horizontal. A 15 kg weight is attached to the rope at the midpoint which now no longer remains horizontal. The minimum tension required to completely straighten the rope is :</p>","options":["<p>15 kg</p>","<p>$\\dfrac{15}{2}$ kg</p>","<p>5 kg</p>","<p>Infinitely large (or not possible)</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mqlgl6uz","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":841384381,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>A sphere of mass $m$ is kept between two inclined walls, as shown in the figure. If the coefficient of friction between each wall and the sphere is zero then the ratio of normal reaction $\\left(\\frac{N_1}{N_2}\\right)$ offered by the walls 1 and 2 on the sphere will be</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr6i2mte/855205a9-8ef5-4349-8c9a-2c2bbdd5d105/a04b2e20-77ba-11f1-b778-856c7b75f5bf/file-6y3zli1mr6i2mtf.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr6i2mte/855205a9-8ef5-4349-8c9a-2c2bbdd5d105/a04b2e20-77ba-11f1-b778-856c7b75f5bf/file-6y3zli1mr6i2mtf.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","question":"<p>A sphere of mass $m$ is kept between two inclined walls, as shown in the figure. If the coefficient of friction between each wall and the sphere is zero then the ratio of normal reaction $\\left(\\frac{N_1}{N_2}\\right)$ offered by the walls 1 and 2 on the sphere will be</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr6i2mte/855205a9-8ef5-4349-8c9a-2c2bbdd5d105/a04b2e20-77ba-11f1-b778-856c7b75f5bf/file-6y3zli1mr6i2mtf.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr6i2mte/855205a9-8ef5-4349-8c9a-2c2bbdd5d105/a04b2e20-77ba-11f1-b778-856c7b75f5bf/file-6y3zli1mr6i2mtf.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","options":["<p><b>tan $\\theta$</b></p>","<p><b>tan $2\\theta$</b></p>","<p><b>2 cos $\\theta$</b></p>","<p><b>cos $2\\theta$</b></p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mr6id80r","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":813358142,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>A string is wrapped round a log of wood and it is pulled with a force F as shown in the figure. Choose the correct statement(s).</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7cxvpn/858e52ef-00cb-41f2-a18f-2fdf57fd2741/571f99b0-7833-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7cxvpo.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7cxvpn/858e52ef-00cb-41f2-a18f-2fdf57fd2741/571f99b0-7833-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7cxvpo.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\"><br><p><b>I.</b> Tension T in the string decreases with increase in θ</p><p><b>II.</b> Tension T &gt; F if $\\theta &gt; \\frac{\\pi}{3}$</p>","question":"<p>A string is wrapped round a log of wood and it is pulled with a force F as shown in the figure. Choose the correct statement(s).</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7cxvpn/858e52ef-00cb-41f2-a18f-2fdf57fd2741/571f99b0-7833-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7cxvpo.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7cxvpn/858e52ef-00cb-41f2-a18f-2fdf57fd2741/571f99b0-7833-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7cxvpo.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\"><br><p><b>I.</b> Tension T in the string decreases with increase in θ</p><p><b>II.</b> Tension T &gt; F if $\\theta &gt; \\frac{\\pi}{3}$</p>","options":["<p>only I is true</p>","<p>both are true</p>","<p>only II is true</p>","<p>both are wrong</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mr7d5ox3","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":810504931,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>AB is a string whose one end A is fixed at the highest point of a ring placed in vertical plane. C is the centre of the ring. At other end B of the string, is attached a bead of mass m, which can slide along the ring. If the bead is in equilibrium at B and string is taut then the tension in the string is :</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7d7vbk/cbc3db45-22cc-4434-b566-2cf6f9394fc4/6ce9a500-7834-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7d7vbl.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7d7vbk/cbc3db45-22cc-4434-b566-2cf6f9394fc4/6ce9a500-7834-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7d7vbl.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","question":"<p>AB is a string whose one end A is fixed at the highest point of a ring placed in vertical plane. C is the centre of the ring. At other end B of the string, is attached a bead of mass m, which can slide along the ring. If the bead is in equilibrium at B and string is taut then the tension in the string is :</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7d7vbk/cbc3db45-22cc-4434-b566-2cf6f9394fc4/6ce9a500-7834-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7d7vbl.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7d7vbk/cbc3db45-22cc-4434-b566-2cf6f9394fc4/6ce9a500-7834-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7d7vbl.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","options":["<p>$mg \\sin 2\\theta$</p>","<p>$mg \\cos \\theta$</p>","<p>$2mg \\cos \\theta$</p>","<p>None of these</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mr7dasrl","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":811005319,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>Two smooth cylindrical bars weighing $W$ N each lie next to each other in contact. A similar third bar is placed over the two bars as shown in figure.</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7dds9z/fc8de5db-71cf-4b58-a57e-2c08cdbc3f2a/116a8770-7835-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7ddsa0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7dds9z/fc8de5db-71cf-4b58-a57e-2c08cdbc3f2a/116a8770-7835-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7ddsa0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\"><p>Neglecting friction, the minimum horizontal force on each lower bar necessary to keep them together is :</p>","question":"<p>Two smooth cylindrical bars weighing $W$ N each lie next to each other in contact. A similar third bar is placed over the two bars as shown in figure.</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7dds9z/fc8de5db-71cf-4b58-a57e-2c08cdbc3f2a/116a8770-7835-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7ddsa0.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7dds9z/fc8de5db-71cf-4b58-a57e-2c08cdbc3f2a/116a8770-7835-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7ddsa0.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\"><p>Neglecting friction, the minimum horizontal force on each lower bar necessary to keep them together is :</p>","options":["<p>$\\dfrac{W}{2}$</p>","<p>$W$</p>","<p>$\\dfrac{W}{\\sqrt{3}}$</p>","<p>$\\dfrac{W}{2\\sqrt{3}}$</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mr7dpy6w","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":814498824,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>Two blocks of mass 6 kg and 4 kg are pushed along a horizontal frictionless surface by a force of 40 N applied to the 6 kg block at an angle of $60^\\circ$ to the horizontal. The force that the 4 kg block exerts on the 6 kg block is :</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7dsvzk/520b82c3-2584-4ac6-a801-537b58305a9b/b56b6f00-7836-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7dsvzl.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7dsvzk/520b82c3-2584-4ac6-a801-537b58305a9b/b56b6f00-7836-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7dsvzl.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","question":"<p>Two blocks of mass 6 kg and 4 kg are pushed along a horizontal frictionless surface by a force of 40 N applied to the 6 kg block at an angle of $60^\\circ$ to the horizontal. The force that the 4 kg block exerts on the 6 kg block is :</p>\n<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7dsvzk/520b82c3-2584-4ac6-a801-537b58305a9b/b56b6f00-7836-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7dsvzl.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7dsvzk/520b82c3-2584-4ac6-a801-537b58305a9b/b56b6f00-7836-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7dsvzl.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","options":["<p>8N to the left</p>","<p>12N to the left</p>","<p>12N to the right</p>","<p>8N to the right</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"ExamGoal JEE Main 2027","image":null,"_examgoalId":"tq-mr7e02tp","_bank":"examgoal_2027"},{"id":814219308,"subject":"Physics","chapter":"Laws Of Motion","q":"<p>Two trucks pull on either end of a rope, each with a force of 10,000 N. In the centre of the rope, a ball of mass 20 kg is hanging. The angle $\\theta$ that the rope makes with the horizontal is :</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7e288b/a5e55769-ff51-447c-937c-50ae8c733f7f/b928cfb0-7837-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7e288c.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7e288b/a5e55769-ff51-447c-937c-50ae8c733f7f/b928cfb0-7837-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7e288c.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","question":"<p>Two trucks pull on either end of a rope, each with a force of 10,000 N. In the centre of the rope, a ball of mass 20 kg is hanging. The angle $\\theta$ that the rope makes with the horizontal is :</p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/6y3zli1mr7e288b/a5e55769-ff51-447c-937c-50ae8c733f7f/b928cfb0-7837-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7e288c.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/6y3zli1mr7e288b/a5e55769-ff51-447c-937c-50ae8c733f7f/b928cfb0-7837-11f1-9d09-a14152a8f54e/file-6y3zli1mr7e288c.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width: 100%;height: auto;display: block;margin: 0 auto;max-height: 40vh;vertical-align: baseline\">","options":["<p>$56^{\\circ}$</p>","<p>$5.6^{\\circ}$</p>","<p>$0.56^{\\circ}$</p>","<p>$0^{\\circ}$, the rope will obviously be horizontal in this situation</p>"],"answer":0,"solution":"","type":"mcq","questionType":"mcq","source":"Exam